4 SECTION 2. AMENDATORY 26 O.S. 2021, Section 13A-105, is
5 amended to read as follows:
6 Section 13A-105. Candidates for member of the board of
7 education of every school district or technology center school
8 district shall file declarations of candidacy in the same place and
9 with the same officials as candidates for county office. The
10 declaration of candidacy to be signed by the candidate shall have an
11 attachment to be signed by the candidate listing the requirements of
12 a candidate for election or reelection to a school board as set
13 forth in Sections 13A-106 and 5-105a of this title and Sections 5-
14 110, 5-110.1, and 5-113 of Title 70 of the Oklahoma Statutes, and
15 the candidate shall swear or affirm that he or she is eligible to
16 run for the office or serve in the office if elected. Candidates
17 shall list their political party affiliation, or nonpartisan status
18 if running as an independent, which shall appear next to their name
19 on both the primary ballot and the general election ballot.
20 Candidates shall file no earlier than 8:00 a.m. on the first Monday
21 Wednesday in December April through no later than 5:00 p.m. on the
22 following Wednesday next succeeding Friday. For school districts
23 and technology center school districts located in more than one
24 county, filing may be either in the county wherein supervision of
